The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning long-term dependencies in recurrent neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The algorithm involves an attention mechanism and backtracking, which are both topics that are relevant to several subfields of computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category, as the paper is primarily concerned with developing a new learning algorithm. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories, as the paper deals with neural networks and their ability to learn long-term dependencies. cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are less likely but still possible categories, as the paper may have applications in natural language processing or image recognition.
